    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				( More quickly to this point.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						bona fide dictum: sed mala fide factum. 
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Said in good faith: but done in bad faith.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						( Passionis ratio, non rationis. ) 
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				( The reasoning of passion, not of reason. )
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    	
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Omnes vitae, 
    						tria sunt verba, scientia, virtus, et hinc foelicitas: aut
    						his contraria. In genere, spetie, indiuiduo.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				All lives are in three words, namely: knowledge, virtue, and happiness: 
    				or the contrary of these. In genus, in species, and in the individual.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Ars, virtus, praxis, merus aether, spiritus, ignis,
    						vitarum effigies vnica, vita mea est. }
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Skill, virtue, action, pure either, spirit, fire,
    				the sole image of lives: this is my life. }
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="90" place="right_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Plus valet vnus Optimus, vel auctor, vel actor, quàm centum mediocres.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				A single Great man, either as author or actor,  is worth more than one hundred mediocre ones.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
